            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Hd1e108">Rubrica 9</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De litibus et iurgiis</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>
      ¶ De litibus et iurgiis. Rubrica. 9.
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e119">
               <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>SAlomon in prouer. c. 13.
      <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e125">Inter superbos
        <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>semper iurgia sunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e131"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e133"> 17. c. Melior
        <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>est bucella sicca cum gaudio quam do
        <lb ed="#V" n="52" break="no"/>mus plena victimis cum iurgio. Seper iurgia
        <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>quarit malus. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e144"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e146"> 18. c. Os stulti iurgia prouocat. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e150">
               <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e154">¶ Iesus filius sirach in eccl. c. 8. Non litiges
        <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>cum homine potente: ne forte incidas in manus
        <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>illius. Non contendas cum viro locuplete: ne eo
        <lb ed="#V" n="57"/>consistat litem tibi: multos enim perdidit aurum
        <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>et argentum vsque corregum extendit et conuertit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e166">
               <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e170">/ 28. c. Abstine te a lite: et minues peccata.
        <lb ed="#V" n="60"/>Homo iracundus incendit litem. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e176">
               <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e180">¶ Cronica de nugisphilosophurum. c. 6 scilicet de pictago.
        <lb ed="#V" n="62"/>Pictagus mitilenus qui fuit vnus de septem
        <lb ed="#V" n="63"/>sapiententibus dicebat: Non obiurgare amicum
        <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>imo nec inimicum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e190">
               <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e194">¶ Ouidius de arte amandi li. i.
        <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>Iurgia praecipue vino stimulata caueto.
        <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>Est nimium facilis ad fera bella manus. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e202"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e204"> Li. 2
        <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>Esse procul lites: et amare premia lingue. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e211">
               <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e215">/ Paulus apostolus in epistola. 2. ad timotheum. c. 2.
        <lb ed="#V" n="70"/>Seruum deo non oportet litigare: sed mansue
        <lb ed="#V" n="71" break="no"/>tum esse ad omnes: docibilem: patientem: cum mo
        <lb ed="#V" n="72" break="no"/>destia corripientem eos qui resistunt veritati. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e225">
               <lb ed="#V" n="73"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e229">¶ Seneca de ira li. 2. Cum pari contendere an
        <lb ed="#V" n="74" break="no"/>ceps est: cum superiore furiosum: cum infe
        <lb ed="#V" n="75" break="no"/>riori sordidum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e237">
               <lb ed="#V" n="76"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e241">¶ Paladius de agricultura. c. 6. Uno vel co
        <lb ed="#V" n="77"/>lono consinia possidenti qui fundum aut a
        <lb ed="#V" n="78" break="no"/>grum suum locat: dannis suis ac litibus studet. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e249">
               <lb ed="#V" n="79"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e253">¶ Lex diges. ti. de alienatione iudi. etc. l. item
        <lb ed="#V" n="80"/>si res. in fi. Uerecunda cogitatio eius qui li
        <lb ed="#V" n="81" break="no"/>tes execratur: non est vituperanda. Lex codi. ti.
        <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>de iudi. li. properatur dum. in pn. Sepe cause pecu
        <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>niarie mam criminalibus creare noscuntur. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e265">
               <lb ed="#V" n="84"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e269">¶ Auctor lib. de for. honeste vite. c. 4. Non
        <lb ed="#V" n="85"/>in inurgia disceptationesque descendas. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e275">
               <lb ed="#V" n="86"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e279">¶ Cato. c. 3. Litem inferre caue cum quo ti
        <lb ed="#V" n="87" break="no"/>bi gratia iuncta est. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e286">
               <lb ed="#V" n="88"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e290">¶ Cassiodorus epistolarum li. 4. e. 37. Longa
        <lb ed="#V" n="89"/>questio litigantium non tam auget patri
        <lb ed="#V" n="90" break="no"/>monia quam euertit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e298"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e300"> Lib. i1i1. e. 9. Si queri¬ <!--117.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="45-v"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>tis lucra: vitate potius dannosa litigia. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e312">
               <lb ed="#V" n="2"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e316">¶ Isidorus soliloquiorum lib. 2. c. 25. Nullus
        <lb ed="#V" n="3"/>existat sermo inurgiorum qui concordiam diui
        <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>dat. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e324"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e326"> 26 c. Uita lites. Tolle occasionem liu. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-d1e330">
               <lb ed="#V" n="5"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d34288-Qd1e334">¶ Iacobus beneuentanus. c. 29
        <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>Hoc tibi precipio vites vt placita semper:
        <lb ed="#V" n="7"/>Si poteris: quoniam prelia sepe mouent.
        <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>Questio res minuit: odium creat: incitat. iram.
        <lb ed="#V" n="9"/>Pro lucro damnum: ducere sepe solet. </quote>
            </p>
         </div>
